This paper is about video frame synthesis using a neural network approach, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of multi-scale structure and adversarial training, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of consistency loss, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR) research.
